dct_description_sm: New Jersey. Department of Conservation and Development. Division of Geology and Topography. Atlas Sheet 33 (1937) New Jersey Geological Survey. Relief shown by 10 ft. contour interval and spot heights. Depths are shown by contours and sounding in feet at low tide. Title is not given. Region covered: vicinity of Barnegat Bay. Original survey and revisions to 1884, principal features revised 1905, 1925, and 1936. Original survey and revisions to 1905 made under direction of C. C. Vermeule, Topographer. Revision of 1936 by L. P. Plummer, Topographic Engineer. Inset: southern continuation.
dct_publisher_sm: Trenton, N.J. : New Jersey Geological Survey, 1937.
